I just finished the excruciating experience of eating tacos from Tepache. They lost one start as soon as I saw the tortillas of my Fish, Carnitas, Birria and Tongue tacos. Prepackaged tortillas are an insult to this staple dish, I still can’t wash away the sorbic acid from the preservatives in those tortillas. Another start was lost due to the parched meat in the birria and carnitas tacos. The third start disappeared with the lack of limes in my order. How dare you sell me tacos without limes included! The fourth start died with the tongue taco, overcooked tongue should never make it into a taco. Finally, I have to leave one start to be able to leave this review and warning to future clients. If you’re looking for tacos, Taqueria Al Pastor in Bushwick is superb.

I have been ordering from this Restaurant from day one. This restaurant became my family and I preferred restaurant in our community. They had superb food. Unfortunately, I am sad to report that they are cutting corners to perhaps cut costs. The rice is parboiled which is the nastiest rice ever. My favorite plate The Mole Enchiladas tastes so different. It is poorly cooked with bad ingredients. Mole is one of the most exquisite Pre Hispanic Foods that you can taste. Unfortunately this restaurant has lowered the grade of this Mexican National Dish. The tacos were good size now they are smallest tacos I have ever eaten. My favorite is the Beef Barbacoa Taco. These tacos were super delicious, the meat was moist and super tender that I melted in your tongue. Now the taco is dry and tough.  I love to support my local business especially those run and owned by Minorities. This restaurant no longer has my support. I have tasted better food and cooking from this restaurant when it started. Have they lowered the costs and with it they have lowered the grade and taste of the food? Absolutely YES! I withdraw my support to this restaurant.
